article.headline: Charlotte 62, Dayton 49
article.story: CHARLOTTE, N.C. (AP) -- Curtis Withers had his 12th double-double of the season with 23 points and a career-high 21 rebounds to lead Charlotte to a 62-49 victory over Dayton Saturday in the Atlantic-10 Conference. De'Angelo Alexander had 15 points and 7 rebounds for the 49ers (13-8, 6-3), while Leemire Goldwire shut down Dayton's leading scorer Brian Roberts in the second half. Roberts still led the Flyers (11-12, 3-6) with 22 points. Norman Plummer finished with 11. Charlotte trailed 28-21 at the half when coach Bobby Lutz decided to make sure Withers touched the ball on almost every possession in the second half. Withers then scored 13 of Charlotte's first 18 points of the half. The 49ers quickly erased the 7-point deficit and took the lead for good with 9:04 to go when Withers grabbed an offensive rebound and scored on a powerful slam dunk. Dayton shot just 23.3 percent from the field in the second half and seemed to have no answers offensively. The Flyers were without their second-leading scorer, Monty Scott, who was out with a stress fracture in his left foot.
